what: Adding hypothetical samples for more plausible evolutionary scenarios
title: Introduction to Jellyfisher
text: feature mainly useful multiple time points present, since subclones appear across several branches sample tree may otherwise LCA placed inferred root. technically correct, suggests subclone emerged real samples, may sometimes biologically implausible. address , can insert hypothetical inferred sample sample tree use new parent subset samples. creates plausible location LCA often yields clearer evolutionary scenario. mechanism can also used generally organize sample tree diverging clades displayed structured way. following example, samples Diagnosis Interval time points patient EOC153 contain distinct clades. original subclones apparently eradicated treatment, new subclones emerged interval debulking surgery. Without manually inserted inferred sample, interval subclones’ LCA placed inferred root, suggesting unlikely evolutionary scenario. adding hypothetical intermediate sample, can anchor emergence subclones realistic position sample tree. add_inferred_sample() function performs three actions: Creates new inferred sample given name rank. Sets parent specified samples. Updates sample tree subclone LCAs can placed new node. resulting plot shows subclones emerging newly introduced sample, diagnosis relapse time points, producing realistic interpretable evolutionary scenario.
code: jellyfisher_example_tables |>   select_patients("EOC153") |>   add_inferred_sample(     name = "EOC153_Inf",     rank = 3,     samples = c(       "EOC153_iPer1_DNA4",       "EOC153_iOme1_DNA4",       "EOC153_iOvaR1_DNA1"     )   ) |>   jellyfisher(width = "100%", height = 600)

title: Introduction to Jellyfisher
text: Typically tumor evolution studies, focus subclonal compositions tumor cells. Thus, root node phylogenetic tree represents founding clone. However, data may also contain non-aberrant cells, .e., tumor purity less 100%. cases, normalsInPhylogenyRoot option instructs Jellyfisher treat root node non-aberrant cells. option two consequences: (1) tentacles drawn root subclones, (2) root subclone colored white phylogeny-aware color scheme used. plot, root clone, represents non-aberrant cells, hidden inferred root sample. However, sometimes patient may multiple independent clones, cases root clone shown:
code: # Subclone N at the root represents the non-aberrant cells. # The letter N has no special meaning in Jellyfisher. non_aberrant <- list(   samples = data.frame(sample = c("A", "B")),   compositions = data.frame(     sample = c("A", "A", "A", "B", "B", "B"),     subclone = c("N", "1", "2", "N", "1", "2"),     clonalPrevalence = c(0.2, 0.4, 0.4, 0.3, 0.3, 0.4)   ),   phylogeny = data.frame(     subclone = c("N", "1", "2"),     parent = c(NA, "N", "1")   ) ) non_aberrant |>   jellyfisher(options = list(     normalsAtPhylogenyRoot = TRUE   ),   width = "100%", height = 350) # Change the parent of subclone 2 to N non_aberrant$phylogeny$parent[non_aberrant$phylogeny$subclone == "2"] <- "N"  non_aberrant |>   jellyfisher(options = list(     normalsAtPhylogenyRoot = TRUE   ),   width = "100%", height = 350)

title: Creates a Jellyfish plot — jellyfisher
text: tables named list data frames. list must contain following elements: samples data frame sample data. expected columns : sample specifies unique identifier sample. (string) displayName allows specifying custom name sample. column omitted, sample column used display name. (string, optional) rank specifies position sample Jellyfish plot. example, different stages disease can ranked chronological order: diagnosis (1), interval (2), relapse (3). zeroth rank reserved root sample tree. Ranks can integer, unused ranks automatically excluded plot. rank column (integer) parent identifies parent sample entry. Samples without specified parent treated children imaginary root sample. (string) phylogeny data frame phylogeny data. expected columns : subclone specifies subclone IDs, can string. (string) parent designates parent subclone. subclone without parent considered root phylogeny. (string) color specifies color subclone. column omitted, colors generated automatically. (string, optional) branchLength specifies length branch leading subclone. length may based , example, number unique mutations subclone. branch length shown Jellyfish plot's legend bar chart. also used generating phylogeny-aware color scheme. (number) compositions data frame subclonal compositions. expected columns : sample specifies sample ID. (string) subclone specifies subclone ID. (string) clonalPrevalence specifies clonal prevalence subclone sample. clonal prevalence proportion subclone sample. clonal prevalences sample must sum 1. (number) ranks optional data frame ranks. expected columns : rank specifies rank number. zeroth rank reserved inferred root sample tree. However, free define title . (integer) title specifies title rank. (string) options named list options configure plot. Available options: crossingWeight Weight tentacle bundles two pairs samples crossing . Defaults 10. pathLengthWeight Weight total length paths (tentacle bundles) connecting samples. Defaults 2. orderMismatchWeight Weight mismatch order samples. order based "phylogenetic center mass" computed subclonal compositions. Defaults 2. bundleMismatchWeight Weight mismatch placement bundles. "optimal" placement based subclonal compositions, placement may produce excessively long tentacle bundles. Defaults 3. divergenceWeight Weight sum divergences adjacent samples. Defaults 4. bellTipShape shape bell tip. 0 sharp tip, 1 blunt tip. Defaults 0.1. bellTipSpread much spread nested bell tips. 0 spread, 1 full spread. Defaults 0.5. bellStrokeWidth width strokes bell. Defaults 1. bellStrokeDarkening much stroke color bells darkened. Defaults 0.6. bellPlateauPos bell fully appeared plateau starts. Defaults 0.7. sampleHeight Height real sample nodes Defaults 110. sampleWidth Width sample nodes Defaults 90. inferredSampleHeight Height inferred sample nodes Defaults 120. gapHeight Height gaps samples. Gaps routes tentacle bundles. Defaults 60. sampleSpacing Vertical space samples Defaults 60. columnSpacing Horizontal space columns Defaults 90. tentacleWidth Width tentacles pixels Defaults 2. tentacleSpacing Space tentacles bundle, pixels Defaults 5. inOutCPDistance Relative distance tentacle control points edge sample node Defaults 0.3. bundleCPDistance Relative distance tentacle bundle's control points. higher value, longer individual tentacles stay together diverging. Defaults 0.6. sampleFontSize Font size sample labels Defaults 12. showLegend Whether show legend Defaults TRUE. phylogenyColorScheme Whether use color scheme based phylogeny Defaults TRUE. phylogenyHueOffset Offset hue phylogeny color scheme. automatically generated hues liking, can adjust hue offset get different color scheme. Defaults 0. phylogenyLightnessStart Lightness root phylogeny Defaults 0.94. phylogenyLightnessEnd Lightness divergent leaf phylogeny Defaults 0.68. phylogenyChromaStart Chroma root phylogeny Defaults 0.025. phylogenyChromaEnd Chroma divergent leaf phylogeny Defaults 0.21. sampleTakenGuide Type "sample taken" guide. "none" guides, "line" faint dashed line samples, "text" line, text label one samples. "text-" text, text label samples. Defaults "text". showRankTitles Whether show rank titles samples (provided). Defaults TRUE. normalsAtPhylogenyRoot Whether root phylogenetic tree contains normal cells. true, tentacles drawn root clone color white phylogenyColorScheme used. Defaults FALSE. controls optional parameter set initial state controls. Can "open", "closed", "hidden". width width widget height height widget elementId optional element ID widget

title: Jellyfisher example data — jellyfisher_example_tables
text: named list data frames containing following tables: samples data frame sample data. Columns : sample specifies unique identifier sample. (string) displayName allows specifying custom name sample. column omitted, sample column used display name. (string, optional) rank specifies position sample Jellyfish plot. example, different stages disease can ranked chronological order: diagnosis (1), interval (2), relapse (3). zeroth rank reserved root sample tree. Ranks can integer, unused ranks automatically excluded plot. rank column (integer) parent identifies parent sample entry. Samples without specified parent treated children imaginary root sample. (string) phylogeny data frame phylogeny data. Columns : subclone specifies subclone IDs, can string. (string) parent designates parent subclone. subclone without parent considered root phylogeny. (string) color specifies color subclone. column omitted, colors generated automatically. (string, optional) branchLength specifies length branch leading subclone. length may based , example, number unique mutations subclone. branch length shown Jellyfish plot's legend bar chart. also used generating phylogeny-aware color scheme. (number) compositions data frame subclonal compositions. Columns : sample specifies sample ID. (string) subclone specifies subclone ID. (string) clonalPrevalence specifies clonal prevalence subclone sample. clonal prevalence proportion subclone sample. clonal prevalences sample must sum 1. (number) ranks optional data frame ranks. Columns : rank specifies rank number. zeroth rank reserved inferred root sample tree. However, free define title . (integer) title specifies title rank. (string)
